canonical:
  title: 東郊値雨
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 黃埃漠漠漲晴旻擧扇西風欲汚人多謝晚雲能作雨半途湔洗滿衣塵
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 東郊値雨
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 黃埃漠漠漲晴旻。擧扇西風欲汚人。多謝晚雲能作雨。半途湔洗滿衣塵。
korean:
  title: 동교 치우
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: |-
    누른 먼지 막막히 개인 하늘에 가득한데
    부채를 드니 서녁 바람이 사람을 더럽히려네
    늦은 구름이 능히 비를 일으켜
    노상에서 옷에 가득한 티끌 씻어 줌이 고마워라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0670&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 부채를 …… 더럽히려네 : '
    value: 진(晉)나라 유량(庾亮)과 왕도(王導) 두 사람이 서로 권세를 다투었는데, 유량은 석두(石頭)에 있고, 왕도는 야성(冶城)에 있었다. 왕도가 앉았을 때에 서풍이 크게 불어 티끌을 날리니 왕도가 부채를 들어 티끌을 막으며, “원규(元規 유량(庾亮)의 자(字))의 티끌이 사람을 더럽히네.” 하였다.
english:
  title: Rain at the Eastern Suburb
  author: Kim Keuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Yellow dust swirls thick across the open sky,
    When I raise my fan, the western wind seeks to soil me.
    Thank the tardy clouds for their kindness—
    They wash the road dust from my robes halfway through my journey.
  footnotes:
    - The image of the fan and western wind alludes to a historical anecdote from the Jin Dynasty, where Wang Dao fanned away dust while making a pointed remark about his rival Yu Liang, transforming a mundane gesture into political commentary. Here, the poet invokes this classical reference to express the universal human struggle against nature's indignities.
    - The poem's structure emphasizes the welcome intervention of rain as a form of grace—the clouds arrive not as mere meteorological event but as benevolent force that interrupts the traveler's suffering.
